File: Dis-Chem says it was forced to increase prices of surgical masks because of disruption in supply.  JOHANNESBURG - The Competition Tribunal has wrapped up its hearing on mask price hikes by Dis-Chem. The Competition Commission has slammed Dis-Chem's argument that it increased its prices in March in line with competitors. READ: Dis-Chem denies excessive pricing charge The retailer says it was forced to increase prices of surgical masks because of disruption in supply. It says some suppliers quoted prices up to 40 times higher than the normal price. READ: COVID-19: Dis-Chem charged for inflating prices But the commission says Dis-Chem started hiking its prices for face masks in February, well ahead of competitors and before the procurement costs for this essential item went up. It is unclear when the tribunal will deliver its ruling. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. 